    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Plan-and-Execute Overview"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Plan-and-Execute separates an agent into two distinct roles: a "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Planner"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " that produces a structured step list before any action is taken, and an "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Executor"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " that carries out each step sequentially. A third component \u2014 the "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Re-Planner"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " \u2014 reviews results after each step and revises future steps when the world deviates from what the planner assumed."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Plan-and-Execute architecture: Planner LLM emits a step list; Executor runs steps; Re-Planner revises remaining steps; Final Answer when done",
          "title": "Plan-and-Execute loop: separate planner and executor with optional re-planning after each step"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "The key insight: planning and execution require different capabilities. A planner must reason globally about the goal; an executor must reason locally about a single action and the tools at its disposal. Separating them leads to higher-quality results for both."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Core Data Structures"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Plan"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " holds the goal and a list of "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Step"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " objects. Steps track their execution status so re-planning can see exactly what is done and what remains:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from dataclasses import dataclass, field\nfrom typing import Optional\n\n@dataclass\nclass Step:\n    index: int\n    instruction: str\n    result: Optional[str] = None\n    status: str = \"pending\"  # pending | done | failed\n\n@dataclass\nclass Plan:\n    goal: str\n    steps: list[Step] = field(default_factory=list)\n\n    def pending(self) -> list[Step]:\n        return [s for s in self.steps if s.status == \"pending\"]\n\n    def completed(self) -> list[Step]:\n        return [s for s in self.steps if s.status == \"done\"]\n\n    def context_so_far(self) -> str:\n        \"\"\"Format completed steps as context for executor.\"\"\"\n        if not self.completed():\n            return \"No steps completed yet.\"\n        lines = []\n        for s in self.completed():\n            lines.append(f\"Step {s.index}: {s.instruction}\")\n            lines.append(f\"Result: {s.result[:300] if s.result else '(none)'}\\n\")\n        return \"\\n\".join(lines)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Planner: Creating the Initial Plan"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The planner receives the goal and returns an ordered step list. The prompt enforces that each step is independently executable and that the total count stays manageable. Returning structured JSON makes parsing reliable:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "PLAN_PROMPT = \"\"\"\nYou are a planning agent. Break the following goal into a numbered list\nof concrete, sequential steps. Each step should be independently executable\nby an agent that has access to web search, code execution, and file tools.\n\nGoal: {goal}\n\nReturn JSON:\n{{\"steps\": [\"step 1 description\", \"step 2 description\", ...]}}\n\nRules:\n- Each step is a single, specific action (not a broad phase).\n- Steps that depend on previous results must come after them.\n- Maximum 8 steps. Aim for 4-6.\n\"\"\"\n\ndef create_plan(goal: str) -> Plan:\n    response = client.messages.create(\n        model=\"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\n        max_tokens=1024,\n        messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": PLAN_PROMPT.format(goal=goal)}],\n    )\n    data = json.loads(response.content[0].text)\n    steps = [\n        Step(index=i + 1, instruction=desc)\n        for i, desc in enumerate(data[\"steps\"])\n    ]\n    return Plan(goal=goal, steps=steps)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Prompt engineering note:"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " tell the planner to emit steps that are concrete and tool-actionable, not high-level phases like 'Research the topic.' Vague steps produce vague executor outputs."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Executor: Running One Step"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The executor receives the full goal, the context of what has been done so far, and a single step instruction. Injecting prior results as context allows later steps to build on earlier ones without the executor needing global knowledge:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "EXECUTE_PROMPT = \"\"\"\nYou are an execution agent with the following tools: web_search, run_code, read_file.\n\nOverall goal: {goal}\n\nWork completed so far:\n{context}\n\nYour current task (step {index} of {total}):\n{instruction}\n\nComplete this step and return only the result. Be concise.\n\"\"\"\n\ndef execute_step(plan: Plan, step: Step) -> str:\n    prompt = EXECUTE_PROMPT.format(\n        goal=plan.goal,\n        context=plan.context_so_far(),\n        index=step.index,\n        total=len(plan.steps),\n        instruction=step.instruction,\n    )\n    response = client.messages.create(\n        model=\"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\n        max_tokens=2048,\n        messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": prompt}],\n    )\n    return response.content[0].text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The context window grows as steps complete. For long plans, truncate old results ("
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "s.result[:300]"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ") to stay within token limits while preserving enough signal for the executor to orient itself."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Re-Planner: Adapting to New Information"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The re-planner runs after each completed step and may revise the remaining steps based on what the executor found. Common triggers: the step result reveals that a planned step is unnecessary, the approach needs to change, or an unexpected dependency was discovered:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "REPLAN_PROMPT = \"\"\"\nThe original plan for the goal below has been partially executed.\nReview the completed steps and their results, then decide:\n  a) Continue with the remaining steps as-is.\n  b) Replace the remaining steps with a revised list.\n\nGoal: {goal}\n\nCompleted steps:\n{completed}\n\nRemaining steps (may be revised):\n{remaining}\n\nReturn JSON:\n{{\"action\": \"continue\" | \"revise\",\n  \"steps\": [\"revised step 1\", ...]  <- only required if action=revise\n}}\n\"\"\"\n\ndef replan_if_needed(plan: Plan) -> Plan:\n    remaining = plan.pending()\n    if not remaining:\n        return plan\n\n    completed_text = plan.context_so_far()\n    remaining_text = \"\\n\".join(f\"{s.index}. {s.instruction}\" for s in remaining)\n\n    response = client.messages.create(\n        model=\"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\n        max_tokens=512,\n        messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": REPLAN_PROMPT.format(\n            goal=plan.goal,\n            completed=completed_text,\n            remaining=remaining_text,\n        )}],\n    )\n    data = json.loads(response.content[0].text)\n    if data[\"action\"] == \"revise\":\n        next_idx = remaining[0].index\n        new_steps = [\n            Step(index=next_idx + i, instruction=desc)\n            for i, desc in enumerate(data[\"steps\"])\n        ]\n        # Replace remaining pending steps with revised ones\n        plan.steps = plan.completed() + new_steps\n        print(f\"Re-planned: {len(new_steps)} steps replace {len(remaining)}\")\n    return plan"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The re-planner preserves completed steps unchanged \u2014 only pending steps are up for revision. This ensures earlier results remain the canonical record of work done."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Full Loop: Putting It Together"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The main loop picks the first pending step, executes it, optionally re-plans, and repeats until no pending steps remain. A final synthesis step consolidates all results into a cohesive answer:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "SYNTHESIZE_PROMPT = \"\"\"\nThe following goal has been completed step-by-step.\nSynthesize a final answer from the collected results.\n\nGoal: {goal}\n\nCompleted steps and results:\n{context}\n\nWrite a clear, concise final answer that directly addresses the goal.\n\"\"\"\n\ndef run_plan_and_execute(\n    goal: str,\n    replan_after_each_step: bool = True,\n) -> str:\n    plan = create_plan(goal)\n    print(f\"Plan ({len(plan.steps)} steps):\")\n    for s in plan.steps:\n        print(f\"  {s.index}. {s.instruction}\")\n\n    while plan.pending():\n        step = plan.pending()[0]\n        print(f\"Executing step {step.index}: {step.instruction}\")\n        step.result = execute_step(plan, step)\n        step.status = \"done\"\n\n        if replan_after_each_step:\n            plan = replan_if_needed(plan)\n\n    # Synthesize final answer from all results\n    response = client.messages.create(\n        model=\"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\n        max_tokens=2048,\n        messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": SYNTHESIZE_PROMPT.format(\n            goal=goal,\n            context=plan.context_so_far(),\n        )}],\n    )\n    return response.content[0].text\n\n# Example:\n# answer = run_plan_and_execute(\n#     \"Find three Python libraries for async HTTP and compare their performance\"\n# )"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Adaptive Re-Planning"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Re-planning after every step adds latency and LLM cost. A more efficient approach is "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "signal-driven re-planning"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ": only re-plan when the executor signals it is necessary, or on a periodic health-check interval:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "def run_plan_and_execute_adaptive(\n    goal: str,\n    max_steps: int = 12,\n) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Plan-and-Execute with adaptive re-planning and step budget.\n\n    Re-planning only triggers when a step result contains an explicit\n    signal (\"REPLAN_NEEDED\") or when the result contradicts the plan.\n    Avoids re-planning overhead on every step.\n    \"\"\"\n    plan = create_plan(goal)\n    total_steps = 0\n\n    while plan.pending() and total_steps < max_steps:\n        step = plan.pending()[0]\n        step.result = execute_step(plan, step)\n        step.status = \"done\"\n        total_steps += 1\n\n        # Only re-plan on explicit signal or near step budget\n        needs_replan = (\n            \"REPLAN_NEEDED\" in (step.result or \"\")\n            or total_steps % 3 == 0  # every 3rd step as health-check\n        )\n        if needs_replan:\n            plan = replan_if_needed(plan)\n\n    if plan.pending():\n        print(f\"Warning: {len(plan.pending())} steps skipped (budget exhausted)\")\n\n    response = client.messages.create(\n        model=\"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\n        max_tokens=2048,\n        messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": SYNTHESIZE_PROMPT.format(\n            goal=goal, context=plan.context_so_far())}],\n    )\n    return response.content[0].text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "REPLAN_NEEDED"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " signal is a convention you establish in the executor's prompt: 'If the result requires revising the remaining plan, include the token REPLAN_NEEDED in your output.' This keeps re-planning cheap while ensuring adaptation when it matters."
          }
        ]
      },
